Use an if at the end of the list comprehension (a filter) in order to completely exclude an item from the list.  For example, if you wanted to do this as a list comprehension:
result = []
for i in range(10):
    if i % 2:
        result.append("two")
    elif i % 3:
        result.append("three")
    else:
        pass  # note that you do not actually need this "else" at all

you could do:
result = ["two" if i % 2 else "three" for i in range(10) if i % 2 or i % 3]

