AnswerBody:
Could be happening because of trying to do calculations of mismatching types.
Most likely it‚Äôs because you‚Äôre multiplying ‚Äò_Time.y‚Äô by ‚Äòfloat4 _Speed‚Äô.
float4 _Intensity; 
float4 _Speed; 

// vs

// Incorrect arguments because 
// you‚Äôre implicitly calling: ‚Äòfixed2(x, y + (a * (p, q, r, s));‚Äô // error
fixed2 uvs = fixed2(i.uv.x, i.uv.y + (_Time.y * _Speed));

Same thing for line 62 and Intensity

Cast: Try casting to native HLSL types such as ‚Äòfloat2‚Äô. They are more precise than ‚Äòfixed‚Äô, which only usually takes 11 bits or make Speed and Intensity float

Debugging: Try removing ‚ÄôTime‚Äô and ‚ÄòSpeed‚Äô variables one by one and running each time to see if one of them makes the error or both.


